		<idAbs>The wetland point dataset consists of digitized wetland point identifiers and associated attribute data.  The dataset represents both both inventoried and certified, at locations determined by NRCS. Wetland points were digitized on-screen using Esri ArcGIS software and generally indicate the approximate center of a wetland basin.  Actual boundaries of the inventoried or certified wetland are not represented in this dataset.  NRCS Form CPA-026 and associated maps are the official authoritative source documents concerning the approximate location of the wetland type.  FSA maintains the wetland point dataset on behalf of NRCS in absence of a nationwide polygon dataset of wetland determinations.  Wetland points are typically represented by red, green or yellow symbols based on wetland type on FSA-produced maps provided to agricultural producers for acreage reporting purposes.</idAbs>
		<idPurp>Wetland points are used to identify approximate locations of inventoried and certified wetlands as determined by NRCS to administer USDA farm commodity support and conservation programs</idPurp>
		<idCredit>United States Department of Agriculture, Farm Service Agency, Natural Resources Conservation Service</idCredit>
